{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01FoV6638RNCSPBPZ76rEseG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Msudz9jbAMJ9rJXSJjfzS9","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/BLAST_RADIUS.md","content":"# CVE-2021-23337 Blast Radius Analysis: lodash `_.template` Command Injection\n\n## 1. CVE Identification\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **CVE ID** | CVE-2021-23337 |\n| **Package** | `lodash` (npm) |\n| **Vulnerable Range** | `< 4.17.21` |\n| **Fixed Version** | `4.17.21` |\n| **Severity** | High (CVSS 7.2) |\n| **Vector** | Command injection via `_.template()` |\n\n### Vulnerability Description\n\nThe vulnerability exists in lodash's `_.template()` function. When the `variable` option is user-supplied, the value is embedded directly into a dynamically-constructed `Function()` body without sanitization:\n\n```js\n// lodash.js line 14865 (v4.17.20 — VULNERABLE)\nvar variable = hasOwnProperty.call(options, 'variable') && options.variable;\n// ...\nsource = 'function(' + (variable || 'obj') + ') {\\n' + ...\nreturn Function(importsKeys, sourceURL + 'return ' + source).apply(...)\n```\n\nAn attacker who controls the `variable` option can inject arbitrary JavaScript that executes in the context of the Node.js process. The fix in `4.17.21` added input validation to reject malicious `variable` values.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Direct Dependents\n\nRepos in the workspace that declare `lodash` as a direct dependency in their `package.json`:\n\n### `/workspace/lodash/package.json`\n- **Role**: The lodash source repository itself\n- **Version**: `4.17.20` ← **VULNERABLE** (source code on disk is the vulnerable version)\n\n### `/workspace/webpack/package.json`\n- **Dependency type**: `devDependencies`\n- **Declared range**: `^4.17.19`\n- **Lock file** (`yarn.lock`) resolved version: `4.17.21` ← **PATCHED**\n\n### `/workspace/jest/examples/manual-mocks/package.json`\n- **Dependency type**: `dependencies`\n- **Declared range**: `^4.17.19`\n- **Lock file** (`jest/yarn.lock`) resolved version: `4.17.21` ← **PATCHED**\n\n---\n\n## 3. Transitive Dependency Paths\n\nAll transitive consumers below are resolved to `4.17.21` via the single locked entry in each repo's `yarn.lock`.\n\n### In `/workspace/jest` (yarn.lock)\n\n| Intermediate Package | lodash Range Declared | Chain |\n|----------------------|-----------------------|-------|\n| `@babel/core@7.12.9` | `^4.17.19` | jest-monorepo → @babel/core → lodash |\n| `@microsoft/api-extractor` | `~4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → @microsoft/api-extractor → lodash |\n| `@react-native-community/cli@^8.0.3` | `^4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → @react-native-community/cli → lodash |\n| `@react-native-community/cli-platform-android` | `^4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → @react-native-community/cli-platform-android → lodash |\n| `@react-native-community/cli-platform-ios` | `^4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → @react-native-community/cli-platform-ios → lodash |\n| `@react-native-community/cli-tools` | `^4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → @react-native-community/cli-tools → lodash |\n| `benchmark` | `^4.17.4` | jest-monorepo → benchmark → lodash |\n| `cheerio@1.0.0-rc.3` | `^4.15.0` | jest-monorepo → cheerio → lodash |\n| `conventional-changelog-core` | `^4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → conventional-changelog-core → lodash |\n| `conventional-changelog-writer` | `^4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → conventional-changelog-writer → lodash |\n| `conventional-commits-parser` | `^4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → conventional-commits-parser → lodash |\n| `git-raw-commits` | `^4.17.15` | jest-monorepo → git-raw-commits → lodash |\n| `html-webpack-plugin` | `^4.17.21` | jest-monorepo → html-webpack-plugin → lodash |\n| `inquirer` | `^4.17.21` | jest-monorepo → inquirer → lodash |\n| `node-emoji` | `^4.17.21` | jest-monorepo → node-emoji → lodash |\n| `pretty-error` | `^4.17.20` | jest-monorepo → pretty-error → lodash |\n| `renderkid` | `^4.17.21` | jest-monorepo → renderkid → lodash |\n| `wait-on` | `^4.17.21` | jest-monorepo → wait-on → lodash |\n| `webpack-bundle-analyzer` | `^4.17.20` | jest-monorepo → webpack-bundle-analyzer → lodash |\n| `workbox-build` | `^4.17.20` | jest-monorepo → workbox-build → lodash |\n| `@docusaurus/core` | `^4.17.21` | jest-monorepo → @docusaurus/core → lodash |\n| `@docusaurus/plugin-*` (multiple) | `^4.17.21` | jest-monorepo → @docusaurus/* → lodash |\n\n### In `/workspace/webpack` (yarn.lock)\n\n| Intermediate Package | lodash Range Declared | Chain |\n|----------------------|-----------------------|-------|\n| `@typescript-eslint/typescript-estree@4.8.2` | `^4.17.15` | webpack → @typescript-eslint/typescript-estree → lodash |\n| `benchmark` | `^4.17.4` | webpack → benchmark → lodash |\n| `eslint-plugin-jsdoc` | `^4.17.21` | webpack → eslint-plugin-jsdoc → lodash |\n| `json-schema-to-typescript` | `^4.17.15` | webpack → json-schema-to-typescript → lodash |\n| `whatwg-url` | `^4.7.0` | webpack → whatwg-url → lodash |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Version Analysis\n\n| Consumer | Declared Range | Resolved Version | Status |\n|----------|---------------|-----------------|--------|\n| `/workspace/lodash` (source) | N/A — this IS lodash | `4.17.20` | **VULNERABLE** |\n| `/workspace/webpack` (direct devDep) | `^4.17.19` | `4.17.21` (yarn.lock) | PATCHED |\n| `/workspace/jest/examples/manual-mocks` (direct dep) | `^4.17.19` | `4.17.21` (yarn.lock) | PATCHED |\n| All transitive consumers in jest | various `^4.17.x` / `~4.17.15` | `4.17.21` (single locked entry) | PATCHED |\n| All transitive consumers in webpack | various `^4.17.x` / `^4.7.0` | `4.17.21` (single locked entry) | PATCHED |\n\n### Key Finding\n\nBoth `jest` and `webpack` lock files collapse all lodash ranges into a single resolved version `4.17.21` — the patched release. This means **if node_modules are installed strictly from the lock files, neither repo is exposed at runtime**.\n\nHowever, the **lodash source repository itself** (`/workspace/lodash`) contains version `4.17.20` on disk. This is the pre-fix source code containing the vulnerable `_.template()` implementation. Any process that builds from or directly uses this source (rather than installing from npm) would be running vulnerable code.\n\n### Vulnerable Code Location\n\n`/workspace/lodash/lodash.js` lines 14863–14895 — the `_.template()` function's `variable` option is embedded unsanitized into a `Function()` constructor call.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1534,"cache_read_input_tokens":41348,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1534},"output_tokens":18,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8129fc6-a513-4702-85a9-f35b387ecb92","uuid":"6ab62824-5264-4780-a39f-133f6e9b22fa"}
